@node proj_anti "ignition - Column & Row Titles"
@toc project
The row and column titles indicating the position and addressing of cells within the sheet. Columns are identified by sequential letters (a-z, aa-zz, ...), while rows are sequentially numbered.
You get the cell in column "a" and row 5 by "a5".
Furthermore, you can specify names for the column and row titles, which you can also use to address cells, or as field names for databases.

If you click with the left mouse button in the border between two titles, you can alter the size of the field by dragging the mouse around while you hold down the mouse button.

With the context menu for the titles (right click), you can also insert or remove new rows/columns in the default configuration.

You can find an overview over all other components in this window @{" here " link project}.
@endnode


@node proj_table "ignition - Sheet"
@toc project
This is a view to the actual sheet. Just click on a cell to activate it; when you start entering text, it will be inserted into the current cell (appended to the contents of the cell).
Cells and graphical objects have their own context menus which you can reach by
pressing the right mouse button when hovering above such an object.

You can find an overview over all other components in this window @{" here " link project}.
@endnode


