@node window_cell_size "ignition - Window «Cell Size»"
@toc windows
You can exactly alter the size of the cells at this place. For the cell width as well as its height, among the following options can be chosen:
 - "do not change"
   The size won't be changed.

 - "exact"
   Changes the size of the selected cells to exactly this value (a value
   following a unit, like "1 cm").
   Note, all cells in a row do have the same height, and all cells in a
   column the same width.

 - "minimal"
   Enlarges all cells that are smaller than the specified value - that
   only really makes sense when more than one cell is selected.

 - "optimal"
   Adapts the cell size in a way that the complete contents are visible
   within the cell - the cell width will be determined by the length of
   the text, the cell height by the font size used in the cell.

The changes are applied to all currently selected cells, which are not necessarily the same as those which were selected when the window was opened.

A simple way to change the size of a cell is to press the left mouse button in the space at the borders of a cell title - you can just drag the size to your satisfaction.
@endnode


@node window_notes "ignition - Window «Attach Note»"
@toc windows
Sie können jeder Zelle eine Notiz zuweisen, die dann gezeigt wird, wenn der Mauszeiger über der Zelle zur Ruhe kommt. Die Notiz kann mehrere Zeilen haben, Sie können die gleiche Notiz auch mehreren Zellen zuweisen, und sie auch einfach wieder löschen.

The changes are applied to all currently selected cells, which are not necessarily the same as those which were selected when the window was opened.
@endnode


