* 2.6. Help Bar                                                                   *
***********************************************************************************

@node helpbar "ignition - Help Bar"
@{b}2.6. Help Bar@{ub}

In this bar status informations and help texts, and cell notes are displayed.
You can enable or hide the bar in @{" Preferences - Display " link window_prefs_display}.

At its right border, the following status informations are visible permanently:
 @{b}inter@{ub} - @{" interactive mode " link mode_interactive}
 @{b}edit@{ub} - @{" editing mode " link mode_edit}

In the interactive mode, objects are performing assigned actions, and can be used like other user interface components if the object is of that type (i.e. the button object would be an example for that).
If you are in the editing mode, you can only add/remove or change these objects.

@{u}    @{uu}

@rem
#ifdef IGNITION_LITE_EDITION
@{" Switch to interactive mode " rxs "address ignition.1 interactive set"} @{" Switch to editing mode " rxs "address ignition.1 interactive none"}
#endif
@{" Open window «Preferences - Display» " rxs "address ignition.1 prefs display req"}

@endnode


@node mode_interactive "ignition - Interactive Mode"
In the interactive mode, the actions that have been assigned to the objects in the document can be triggered, defined events can be executed.
On the other hand, you can alter the document in a very restricted way only. For example, you cannot select any cell blocks or objects.

See also @{"Editing Mode" link mode_edit}.

@{u}    @{uu}

@{" Switch to interactive mode " rxs "address ignition.1 interactive set"} @{" Switch to editing mode " rxs "address ignition.1 interactive none"}

@endnode

 
@node mode_edit "ignition - Editing Mode"
In this mode, all editing functions are available and working. New objects can be added and existing ones can be altered. Actions assigned to these objects are not triggered, though; if you click on a button, you only select the object, but its assigned action won't be executed.

See also @{"Interactive Mode" link mode_interactive}.

@{u}    @{uu}

@{" Switch to interactive mode " rxs "address ignition.1 interactive set"} @{" Switch to editing mode " rxs "address ignition.1 interactive none"}

@endnode

 
